==English==
===Etymology===
From Latinised {{Gr.}} [[collectus]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[συλλεκτός]]''' (''syllectos'') "gathered or brought together", from '''[[συλλέγω]]''' (''syllego'') "bring together, collect, gather, compile", from prefix '''[[συλ-]]''' (''syl-'') "with, along with, accompanied by, in, at the same time" + '''[[λέγω]]''' (''lego'') "to gather, pick up, to choose for oneself, pick out, to count."

=== Pronunciation ===
*{{AHD|kō-lĕk'tûr ''or'' kə-lĕk'tûr ''or'' kə-lĕk'tər}}

=== Noun ===
# person or thing which [[collect]]s, or creates or manages a collection
# a person who is employed to collect payments
# the amplified terminal on a Bipolar junction transistor

